text: Warman is a city in Saskatchewan, Canada. It is approximately 5 kilometres (3.1 mi) north of the city of Saskatoon, and 5 kilometres (3.1 mi) northeast of the city of Martensville. Warman is often referred to as a bedroom community of Saskatoon. The current mayor is Sheryl Spence. Warman is the newest city in Saskatchewan, officially incorporated on October 27, 2012. Warman is surrounded by the Rural Municipality of Corman Park No. 344.
